    "The optimal strategy is interaction between physicians and deep learning programmers or developers, either in-house or via collaborative academic agreements [347].Even though the U.S. does not usually require individuals to provide formal documented permission, both prospectively and retroactively collected data must be properly de-identified in order to comply with the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA), or and the European General Data Protection Regulation.",
    "Personal data is frequently contained in the DICOM metadata (header), and there are numerous methods accessible to effectively eliminate this material [348].The last method for anonymizing health data is k-anonymity, which modifies an initial information source including private healthcare data in order to keep prospective hackers from discovering the identify of the individual."
